{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix RLC ASN.1 configuration request handling\n\n### Summary\nThe `rrc_rlc_config_asn1_req` function in the RLC layer had several issues that could cause unexpected behavior when configuring radio bearers:\n\n1. Context validation checks were commented out, allowing invalid context parameters to pass through\n2. MBMS DRB ID calculation didn't properly distinguish between eNB and UE cases\n3. DRB release functionality was unimplemented and would cause the process to exit\n4. Error conditions used `exit(1)` instead of returning proper error codes\n\nThis fix addresses all these issues by:\n- Enabling proper context validation and returning `RLC_OP_STATUS_BAD_PARAMETER` for invalid contexts\n- Fixing MBMS section conditional compilation \n- Implementing proper DRB release functionality with validation\n- Replacing `exit(1)` calls with proper error code returns\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/rlc_v2/rlc_oai_api.c`: Fixed context validation, MBMS handling, DRB release implementation, and error handling\n"
}